ğŸ”§ Systemd Service Setup

Service file location: /etc/systemd/system
File extension: .service

Example: Backend Service
INI[Unit]Description = Backend Service[Service]User=expenseEnvironment=DB_HOST="<MYSQL-SERVER-IPADDRESS>"ExecStart=/bin/node /app/index.jsSyslogIdentifier=backend[Install]WantedBy=multi-user.targetShow more lines

ğŸŒ Nginx Setup

Install:
Shelldnf install nginx -yShow more lines

Config directory: /etc/nginx
Website files: /usr/share/nginx/html
Logs: /var/log/nginx
Default page: /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html


ğŸ§  Concepts
Library

A reusable piece of code that can be consumed by many applications without purchasing.

Proxy Types

Forward Proxy: Client-side proxy, hides client identity.
Reverse Proxy: Server-side proxy, hides server identity (e.g., Nginx).

DNS

Domain Name System â€“ resolves domain names to IP addresses.


ğŸ¬ MySQL Setup for Expense App
Create Database & Table
SQLCREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS transactions;USE transactions;CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS transactions (    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,    amount INT,    description VARCHAR(255));Show more lines
Create User & Grant Permissions
SQLCREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'expense'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'ExpenseApp@1';GRANT ALL ON transactions.* TO 'expense'@'%';FLUSH PRIVILEGES;Show more lines
Import Schema
Shellmysql -h <MYSQL-IP> -uroot -pExpenseApp@1 < /app/schema/backend.sqlShow more lines

